{"id":502191,"url":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Michael_Blake_(author)","text":"Michael Lennox Blake (July 5, 1945 \u2013 May 2, 2015) was an American author and screenwriter. He was best known for the movie adaptation of his novel \"Dances with Wolves\", for which he won an Academy Award and a Golden Globe.\nBlake was born in Fort Bragg, North Carolina, and grew up in New Mexico, Texas and Southern California. He was married and had three sons.\nBlake died after a long illness on May 2, 2015 in Tucson, Arizona. He was 69.","categories":[],"infobox_types":[],"annotations":[{"uri":"Americans","surface_form":"American","offset":57},{"uri":"Author","surface_form":"author","offset":66},{"uri":"Screenwriter","surface_form":"screenwriter","offset":77},{"uri":"Dances_with_Wolves","surface_form":"movie adaptation","offset":117},{"uri":"Dances_with_Wolves_(novel)","surface_form":"Dances with Wolves","offset":148},{"uri":"Academy_Award","surface_form":"Academy Award","offset":189},{"uri":"Golden_Globe","surface_form":"Golden Globe","offset":209},{"uri":"Fort_Bragg%2C_North_Carolina","surface_form":"Fort Bragg","offset":241},{"uri":"North_Carolina","surface_form":"North Carolina","offset":253},{"uri":"New_Mexico","surface_form":"New Mexico","offset":284},{"uri":"Texas","surface_form":"Texas","offset":296},{"uri":"Southern_California","surface_form":"Southern California","offset":306},{"uri":"Tucson%2C_Arizona","surface_form":"Tucson","offset":412},{"uri":"Arizona","surface_form":"Arizona","offset":420}]}